    	<td style="background:url('/img/vlogo.gif') no-repeat bottom right;padding: 0 20px 149px 0;">
		

        	<p><span class="heading"><strong>Careers</strong></span></p>
            
			<p>eVapt is looking to become a significant player in the multi-billion dollar cloud and on-demand market. We are looking for professionals, who excel at their roles, are entrepreneurial in nature, and who have a positive can-do, customer-centric attitude. eVapt provides an open, fun, exciting and driven environment that provides numerous opportunities for growth and professional satisfaction.</p>
			
			<p>See below for current open positions. If there isn't a suitable opening for you at this time, feel free to check in with us again in the near future. Please send resumes to: <a href="mailto:careers@evapt.com">careers@evapt.com</a>.</p>
			<p><div class="hr"></div></p>
			
<h3>Sales Associate (Austin, TX)</h3>

<p>eVapt is the leading provider of metering, billing and subscription management solutions to On Demand / Cloud solutions. This is a great opportunity to join a growing company positioned to be a winner in the Cloud Market Place. </p>

<p>As a Sales Associate you should be able to communicate value, vision and solution to finance, Operations and IT Executives. </p>

<p>Responsibilities:</p>

   <p>1. Generate new leads from outbound calling and emailing</p>
   <p>2. Respond to and qualify incoming leads</p>
   <p>3. Gather information about the needs and pain points of prospects</p>
   <p>4. Follow the selling process and document progress with each qualified opportunity</p>
   <p>5. Must be consistent in achieving quotas</p>
  
<p>Requirements:</p>

   <p>1. 2+ years of software sales experience</p>
   <p>2. Experience selling ERP, CRM or Billing solutions a huge plus</p>
   <p>3. Excellent written and verbal communication skills</p>
   
   <p><div class="hr"></div></p>


<h3>Account Executive - West Coast (Bay Area, CA)</h3>

<p>As a Account Executive you should be able to communicate value, vision and solution to finance, Operations and IT Executives. </p>

Responsibilities:

   <p>1. Generate new leads from outbound calling and emailing</p>
   <p>2. Respond to and qualify incoming leads</p>
   <p>3. Gather information about the needs and pain points of prospects</p>
   <p>4. Follow the selling process and document progress with each qualified opportunity</p>
   <p>5. Conduct web based and face-to-face sales presentations</p>
   <p>6. Conduct product demonstrations</p>
   <p>7. Must be consistent in achieving monthly and quarterly quotas</p>
   <p>8. Must be able to forecast accurately</p>
   <p>9. Must be willing to travel</p>

<p>Requirements:</p>

   <p>1. 4+ years of software sales experience</p>
   <p>2. Consultative selling experience</p>
   <p>3. Experience selling ERP, CRM or Billing solutions a huge plus</p>
   <p>4. Excellent written and verbal communication skills</p>

   <p><div class="hr"></div></p>

<h3>Account Executive - East Coast (Atlanta, New York or Boston)</h3>

<p>As a Account Executive you should be able to communicate value, vision and solution to finance, Operations and IT Executives. </p>

Responsibilities:

   <p>1. Generate new leads from outbound calling and emailing</p>
   <p>2. Respond to and qualify incoming leads</p>
   <p>3. Gather information about the needs and pain points of prospects</p>
   <p>4. Follow the selling process and document progress with each qualified opportunity</p>
   <p>5. Conduct web based and face-to-face sales presentations</p>
   <p>6. Conduct product demonstrations</p>
   <p>7. Must be consistent in achieving monthly and quarterly quotas</p>
   <p>8. Must be able to forecast accurately</p>
   <p>9. Must be willing to travel</p>

<p>Requirements:</p>

   <p>1. 4+ years of software sales experience</p>
   <p>2. Consultative selling experience</p>
   <p>3. Experience selling ERP, CRM or Billing solutions a huge plus</p>
   <p>4. Excellent written and verbal communication skills</p>

   <p><div class="hr"></div></p>

